dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Full tool guide is here: http://rebrand.ly/box4ba8b

This planning tool is a GIS model that that estimates how changes in land use, land management, and land cover affect landscape carbon storage and influence a variety of other potential benefits â€” including agricultural values, water resources, biodiversity and human well-being. The toolis designed to help identify areas where conservation goals are aligned with opportunities to reduce net greenhouse gas emissions.

Planners can use the tool to run scenarios for the entire county or for any defined sub-area within the county. Because the tool is highly configurable, it can be used to model the effects of a wide range of land-use policies, conservation and land-management strategies, and restoration programs.

Detailed activity sheets, which guide implementation of activities at the field level , can be found here for all activities evaluated for the Merced County project: http://rebrand.ly/boxe918b
